HTML - Day 1

HTML - Hyper Text Markup Language.
HTML vs HTML 5
HTML Tags
Head Tag: Meta Tag: information about the document
Body Tag: Contains all of your content

Ex:<h1>B54WD Tamil</h1>
Element: tag + content
above one is called Element
heading tag: h1...h6

P tag: stands for paragraph

To redirect the document, we use a tag/anchor tag.
Ex:
<a href="https://stackoverflow.com/">stackoverflow</a>
href: attribute
attribute: it gives the additional information about tag.
href: represent the link where it has to be redirect
target: help us to open the document on new tab
Ex: <a href="https://github.com/Thiru-cse" target="_blank">Github Profile</a>

Span Tag:
<span style="color: rgb(255, 0, 0);">online learning</span>

Img Tag:
<img src="https://ataglanceanimehome.files.wordpress.com/2020/08/naruto.jpg" style="width: 300px;">

Ol: Order List
Example:
<ol>
        <li>HTML</li>
        <li>CSS</li>
        <li>JavaScript</li>
        <li>ReactJS</li>
</ol>

Ul: Unorder List
Example:

br - break tag

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Day 8 | Learn HTML</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>John</h1>
    <p>john is a full stack developer, willing to explore new things, working at google</p>
    <a href="https://github.com/Thiru-cse" target="_blank">Github Profile</a>
    <h3>Summary</h3>
    <p>GUVI is an IIT-M & IIM-A incubated Ed-tech company that focuses on providing personalized learning solutions for its learners right from <br> 
        <span style="color: rgb(255, 0, 0);">online learning, upskilling & recruitment opportunities</span> in world-class quality. And, bestow tech-skills with the comfort of your native language.</p>
    <img src="https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/69345132?v=4" alt="Naruto" style="width: 300px;">
    <h3>Skills</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>HTML</li>
        <li>CSS</li>
        <li>JavaScript</li>
        <li>ReactJS</li>
    </ul>
    <form>
        <label>Email</label><br>
        <input type="email"><br>
        <label>Password</label><br>
        <input type="password">
    </form>
</body>
</html>

